<TITLE> PM says broadcasting policy, film institute soon </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 14 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has announced establishment of a full-fledged film institute to help make world-class movies in Bangladesh and formulation of national broadcasting policy . She made the announcement on Thursday at the launch of the 10-day Dhaka International Film Festival (DIFF) with the theme "Better Film, Better Audience, Better Society." There is no alternative to gaining knowledge to flourish the industry aesthetically and technologically, she said. Advanced film-making technologies are available nowadays and a modern film institute can impart knowledge on how best to use them, she also said. Hasina asked the culture minister to make a project for a modern institute and said a new censorship of film act will be formulated to replace the 1963 act. Among others, information and culture affairs minister Abul Kalam Azada spoke at the ceremony. b
